## Main parts of plants
- Roots:
	- Structural anchorage
	- Resource absorption and transport
		- Water, nitrogen, nutrients
	- Storage
		- Trees store carbohydrates in roots during winter
- Stems
	- Structural support
	- Resource transport
	- Resource storage
		- Edible stems, IE celery
		- Potatoes
	- Sometimes photosynthesis
- Leaves
	- Food production
	- Transpiration


## Leaves

- Abscission
	- The process through which leaves fall off trees
	- Base of leaves have an abscission zone, which is able to close holes in vascular system
		- Why pruning needs to be done at none
		- ..otherwise will re-sprout

## Stems
![Pasted image 20220907123838.png|200](data:image/png;base64,)
- Typically aboveground
	- Exceptions include bermuda grass
- Can have properties of leaves
	- Can photosynthesize
		- Makes them vulnerable to airborn herbicides
- Can be woody

- Tissues
	- Epidermis
		- Protection
		- Waxy cuticle that revents water loss
		- Trichomes
			- Protection (thorns, prickles)
			- Scent/oil releasing
			- Plants can have multiple types of trichomes interspersed
				- ![Pasted image 20220907124147.png|200](data:image/png;base64,)
	- Vascular bundles
		- Xylem - Conducts water
		- Phloem - Conducts food
		- Both types provide support
		- Vascular cambium
			- Contains meristomatic tissue
				- It's why plants can propagate via cuttings
				- Analogous to stem cells
				- IE if it thinks it's underground and has no roots, it'll grow roots
			- Center of vascular bundle, between xylem and phloem
